654.question: What is the difference in performance between the interpretable system (e.g. vectors and cosine distance) and LSTM with ELMo system?

3-Table1-1.png: The difference in performance between the interpretable system (e.g. vectors and cosine distance) and LSTM with ELMo system is 0.07.</s>

The interpretable system, which includes vectors and cosine distance, has an accuracy of 0.3945 and a perplexity of 907. In contrast, the LSTM with ELMo system has an accuracy of 0.6818 and a perplexity of 706166. This indicates that the LSTM with ELMo system performs significantly better in terms of both accuracy and perplexity compared to the interpretable system.</s>

654.answer: Accuracy of best interpretible system was 0.3945 while accuracy of LSTM-ELMo net was 0.6818.
